hands_on_practices.solution:
We compute the core heating before the crash. With $r_c=\xi a$ and $P_\alpha(r)=\kappa n_\alpha(r)$,
$$
W_{c, \text{before}}
=\int_0^{r_c}P_\alpha(r)\,2\pi r\,dr
=\kappa2\pi n_0\int_0^{r_c}\Bigl(1-\frac{r^2}{a^2}\Bigr)r\,dr
=\kappa2\pi n_0\Bigl[\frac{r^2}{2}-\frac{r^4}{4a^2}\Bigr]_0^{r_c}
=\kappa2\pi n_0a^2\Bigl(\frac{\xi^2}{2}-\frac{\xi^4}{4}\Bigr).
$$

After the crash the density is flattened inside $r_{\text{mix}}=\chi a$ to the average
$$
n_{\text{flat}}
=\frac{\int_0^{r_{\text{mix}}}n_0\,(1-r^2/a^2)\,2\pi r\,dr}{\pi r_{\text{mix}}^2}
=n_0\Bigl(1-\frac{\chi^2}{2}\Bigr).
$$

Thus
$$
W_{c, \text{after}}
=\int_0^{r_c}\kappa n_{\text{flat}}\,2\pi r\,dr
=\kappa2\pi n_0\Bigl(1-\frac{\chi^2}{2}\Bigr)\frac{r_c^2}{2}
=\kappa2\pi n_0a^2\frac{\xi^2}{2}\Bigl(1-\frac{\chi^2}{2}\Bigr).
$$

The fractional change is
$$
\Delta_f
=\frac{W_{c, \text{after}}-W_{c, \text{before}}}{W_{c, \text{before}}}
=\frac{\kappa2\pi n_0a^2\Bigl[\frac{\xi^2}{2}(1-\frac{\chi^2}{2})
-\bigl(\frac{\xi^2}{2}-\frac{\xi^4}{4}\bigr)\Bigr]}
{\kappa2\pi n_0a^2\bigl(\frac{\xi^2}{2}-\frac{\xi^4}{4}\bigr)}
=\frac{\frac{\xi^4}{4}-\frac{\xi^2\chi^2}{4}}{\frac{\xi^2}{2}-\frac{\xi^4}{4}}
=\frac{\xi^2(\xi^2-\chi^2)/4}{\xi^2(2-\xi^2)/4}
=\frac{\xi^2-\chi^2}{2-\xi^2}.
$$
